  "elapsed_s": 11.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And so, of course, we saw the canal.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And at this time, excursion boats were going by.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "People were having cocktails.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I couldn't help but comment how times change, that-- that it just seemed so incongruous, people having such a good time at a place where people were beaten to death, and those helpless victims would fall into the water.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "These canals were very, very useful during World War II.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They had them all over, at least Hannover, and I think certain parts of Germany.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "This saved the German government a lot of money in energy, because right by this-- all the goods that was produced in the factory was taken by slave laborers to these large barges.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And then they would push them down the canal to its destination and-- not having to use gasoline or car or truck or train or whatever.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So while we were at the-- scouting this place, I asked a historian to come along, a German historian, who was very kind and did so.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Dr.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Stuhlberg from the history department of the University of Hannover, who also invited me to speak at the University, wrote a book, which included his entire history department, but students actually who already worked on their secondary degrees, master's or PhDs.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so this book, in two volumes, was written about-- about concentration camps in and around Hannover.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this came about because before the people around Hannover learned that there was a concentration camp, one, And so, just around that time, this neo-Nazi movement started becoming stronger and stronger and historians became concerned.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, some historians became concerned where this may lead to, so they decided in Hannover to do something about it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the professors decided to start right there, in their own backyard.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
